{"text": "I'm recommending this game with a big caveat: It's not anywhere nearly as good as Railway Empire. Worth playing for the sake of variety if you enjoy the genre, but there are some design decisions that are really weird. The lack of control over trains pathing can be really frustrating. They implemented signals only a few months after the launch, and even then it's a very barebones implementations (only directional signals). There's no way to make a route go through a specific railway, or use a specific station track. Sometimes a train will change their pathing seeingly at random, and instead of using a direct track that goes from station A to station B, they will decide to follow a track that goes from A to C to B, causing issues for all other trains along the way.", "appid": "797400", "steamid": "profiles/76561197998827138", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603108800.0}
